# Gitmoji Commits

All commit messages in this project must use the [Gitmoji](https://gitmoji.dev) format.

See `@scottnath/devx` docs for the source of truth:

- `node_modules/@scottnath/devx/docs/gitmoji-rules.md`
- `node_modules/@scottnath/devx/docs/how-to-write-a-commit.md`

## Format

```
<emoji> Short description

Optional body

Optional footer (e.g. issue refs: #123)
```

Use either the raw emoji character or the `:code:` shorthand — both are valid.

## Examples

```
✨ Add demo Astro site with Storybook

🐛 Fix Welcome story args

📝 Update README
```

## Reserved

Do not use `:bookmark:` manually — it is created by semantic-release for version tags.
